com.bmd.android.collection.entry

Interface SparseArrayEntry<V>

  • Type Parameters:
    V - The value type.
    All Superinterfaces:
    IntSparseEntry, IntSparseObjectEntry<V>, SparseEntry, SparseObjectEntry<V>

    public interface SparseArrayEntry<V>
extends IntSparseObjectEntry<V>
    This interface defines a SparseEntry associated with a SparseArray collection.

    Created by davide on 3/10/14.

      • toImmutable

        IntSparseObjectEntry<V> toImmutable()
        Returns an immutable copy of this entry. The object will just store this entry key and value without allowing any modification of the backing sparse collection.
        Returns:
        The immutable entry.

      • toParcelable

        ParcelableIntSparseObjectEntry<V> toParcelable()
        Returns a parcelable copy of this entry. The object will just store this entry key and value without allowing any modification of the backing sparse collection.

        Note that the Parcel.writeValue(Object) function will be called to serialize the entry value. So, if the object does not comply with the specific requirements, the serialization might have unexpected results.

        Returns:
        The parcelable entry.
